Task:

To study the data and find how do annual members and casual riders use Cyclistic bikes differently. Come up with top 3 recommendations to convert casual riders into members.

Data Preparation

# Keeping only required columns
tripdata <- tripdata %>% 
  select(ride_id, rideable_type, started_at, ended_at, member_casual)

# Calculate trip length
tripdata <- tripdata %>% 
  mutate(trip_length = round(difftime(ymd_hms(tripdata$ended_at), ymd_hms(tripdata$started_at), units='mins'), digits = 2))

# Count the occurrences of negative trip length
tripdata %>% 
  filter(trip_length < 0) %>% 
  summarise(n = n())

# Delete the entries with negative trip length
tripdata <- tripdata %>% 
  filter(trip_length >= 0)

# Study trip_length
tripdata %>% 
  summarise(min = min(trip_length), max = max(trip_length), mean = mean(trip_length), sd= sd(trip_length))

quantile(tripdata$trip_length, 0.99)

# Removing entries which are greater than 99 percentile

tripdata <- tripdata%>% 
  filter(trip_length < quantile(trip_length, 0.99))

# Extract trip start day
tripdata <- tripdata %>% 
  mutate (day_of_week = wday(ymd_hms(tripdata$started_at), label=TRUE, abbr=FALSE))

# Extract the month
tripdata <- tripdata %>% 
  mutate (trip_month = month(ymd_hms(ended_at), label = TRUE, abbr=FALSE))

# Extract trip_start hour
tripdata <- tripdata %>% 
  mutate (trip_start_hour = format(ymd_hms(ended_at), format = "%H"))

# Keeping only required columns
tripdata <- tripdata %>% 
  select(ride_id, rideable_type, member_casual, trip_length, day_of_week, trip_month, trip_start_hour)

Data Visualization

# Pie Chart :Number of rides by member_casual
tripdata %>% 
  group_by(member_casual) %>% 
  summarise(total=n()) %>% 
  mutate(per = round((total/sum(total)*100), digits = 2)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = "", y = total, fill = member_casual, label = per))+
  theme_void()+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", alpha = 0.8)+
  geom_text(position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5))+
  coord_polar("y", start=90)+
  labs(title = "Number of rides(percentage) by member_Casual")

# Pie chart: Number of rides by rideable type
tripdata %>% 
  group_by(rideable_type) %>% 
  summarise(total=n()) %>% 
  mutate(per = round((total/sum(total)*100), digits = 2)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = "", y = total, fill = rideable_type, label = per))+
  theme_void()+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", alpha = 0.8)+
  geom_text(position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5))+
  coord_polar("y", start=90)+
  labs(title = "Number of rides(percentage) by rideable type")

# Histogram: Trip length
tripdata %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = as.numeric(trip_length))) +
  theme_bw()+
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, fill = "light blue")+
  geom_vline(xintercept = mean(tripdata$trip_length), col = "red", lwd = 1)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = median(tripdata$trip_length), col = "blue", lwd = 1)+
  annotate("text", 
           x = 40,
           y = 120000,
           label = paste("Mean =", (round(mean(tripdata$trip_length), digits = 2))),
           col = "red",
           size = 4)+
  annotate("text",
           x = 40,
           y = 100000,
           label = paste("Median =", (round(median(tripdata$trip_length), digits = 2))),
           col = "blue",
           size = 4)+
  labs(x = "Trip length",
       y = "No of rides",
       title = "Histogram: Trip length")

# Number of rides by month
tripdata %>% 
  group_by(trip_month) %>% 
  summarise(total=n()) %>% 
  mutate(per = round((total/sum(total)*100), digits = 2)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = trip_month, y = total, fill = trip_month, label = per))+
  theme_bw()+
  geom_col(alpha = 0.5, show.legend = FALSE)+
  geom_text(position = position_stack(vjust = 0.7), size = 3)+
  labs(x = "Month",
       y = "No of rides",
       title = "Number of rides(percentage) by month")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 0.7, hjust=0.5))

# Number of rides by day of week
tripdata %>% 
  group_by(day_of_week) %>% 
  summarise(total=n()) %>% 
  mutate(per = round((total/sum(total)*100), digits = 2)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = day_of_week, y = total, fill = day_of_week, label = per))+
  theme_bw()+
  geom_col(alpha = 0.5, show.legend = FALSE)+
  geom_text(position = position_stack(vjust = 1.05))+
  labs(x = "Day of week",
       y = "No of rides",
       title = "Number of rides(percentage) by day of week")

# Number of rides by hour
ggplot(data = tripdata, aes(x = trip_start_hour))+
  theme_bw()+
  geom_bar(alpha = 0.7)+
  labs(x = "Hour",
       y = "No of rides",
       title = "Number of rides by hour")

# Percentage of casuals and members by rideable type
tripdata %>%
  group_by(rideable_type, member_casual)%>% 
  summarize(total =n())%>% 
  mutate(per = round(total/sum(total)*100, digits = 2))%>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = rideable_type, y = total, fill = member_casual, label = per))+
  theme_bw()+
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', alpha = 0.8, position = "dodge")+
  geom_text(position = position_dodge(width = 0.9), vjust = -0.1)+
  labs(x = "Rideable type",
       y = "No of rides",
       title = "Percentage of casuals and members by rideable type")

Top 3 recommendations

  • 82% of total casual rides are made in 6 months from May to October. Promotions should be run in these months.
  • 39% of total casual rides are made on weekends. Flash sales can be made available on weekends.
  • 73% of total casual rides take place between 10 am to 10 pm. Flash sales can be made available between these hours.

Other recommendations

  • Build marketing strategies around docked bikes as 100% of docked bike users are casual riders.
  • 60 % of rides with trip length greater than 20 minutes are made by casual riders, that is equal to 34% of total casual rides. Special offers can be made to riders with trip length more than 20 minutes.
